# Interaction Patterns — Always Use These

## Selection and Bulk Actions

- Single tap selects, long press enters bulk mode (mobile)
- Floating action bar appears when items are selected
- Always show count: "3 items selected"
- Bulk actions: only show what's valid for ALL selected items

## Destructive Actions

- Require two-step confirmation only if irreversible
- Prefer "Undo" toast (5 second window) over confirm dialogs
- Never use red buttons as primary CTAs
- Label buttons with the action: "Delete Job" not just "Delete"

## Loading States

- Skeleton screens over spinners for list/page loads
- Inline loaders for button actions (button becomes loading state)
- Optimistic UI for simple toggles — update immediately, revert on error

## Empty States (required for every list view)

- Icon + headline + subtext + primary action
- Subtext explains WHY it's empty, not just THAT it's empty
- Primary action is the fastest path to adding content

## Error States

- Inline errors on form fields (not just top-of-form banners)
- Tell user: what went wrong + why + what to do
- Preserve user input on error — never wipe a form

## Navigation (Mobile)

- Bottom sheet for contextual actions (not full-screen modals)
- Swipe to go back always works
- Sticky CTAs at bottom, never buried below fold
- Back button always visible and functional

## Status Indicators

- Color + icon + text label (never color alone)
- Consistent palette: green=complete, yellow=pending, red=urgent/error, blue=in-progress, grey=inactive
